# FEATURE 1: Creative Review Hub (Ad Campaign Engine)
**Repo:** rtmendes/ad-campaign-engine
**Branch:** feature/creative-review-hub
**Target page route:** /review

## 1.1 Problem Statement
Our AI creative pipeline (GPT Image 2, Runway, fal.ai, Remotion, Kong-Killer Copy) generates unlimited ad creatives — but there is NO human quality gate before ads go live. Konstant Kreative's competitive advantage is "real editors + AI" — human editors polish every AI output. We need to clone this workflow as an internal review system.

## 1.2 What We're Building
A **Creative Review Hub** page in the Ad Campaign Engine where:
1. AI-generated creatives land in a review queue automatically
2. A reviewer (Rashida or VA) can approve, reject, or request revision
3. Approved creatives get a quality score and move to "ready" status
4. Rejected creatives get feedback that loops back to AI regeneration
5. Batch review mode for high-volume runs (30+ creatives at once)
6. Before/After comparison view showing original AI output → polished version

## 1.3 New Convex Tables

### Table: `creativeReviews`
```typescript
creativeReviews: defineTable({
  // Link to existing creatives table
  creativeId: v.id("creatives"),
  
  // Review state
  status: v.union(
    v.literal("pending"),       // Just entered queue
    v.literal("in_review"),     // Reviewer is looking at it
    v.literal("approved"),      // Passed QA
    v.literal("rejected"),      // Failed QA — needs rework
    v.literal("revision_requested"), // Minor tweaks needed
    v.literal("auto_approved")  // Score >= 90, bypassed human review
  ),
  
  // Quality scoring (0-100)
  qualityScore: v.optional(v.number()),
  
  // Scoring breakdown
  compositionScore: v.optional(v.number()),     // Layout, visual hierarchy (0-25)
  brandAlignmentScore: v.optional(v.number()),  // On-brand colors, voice, style (0-25)
  copyScore: v.optional(v.number()),            // Headline, CTA, body copy quality (0-25)
  platformFitScore: v.optional(v.number()),     // Correct specs, format, safe zones (0-25)
  
  // Review metadata
  reviewerNotes: v.optional(v.string()),
  rejectionReason: v.optional(v.string()),
  revisionInstructions: v.optional(v.string()),
  
  // AI-assisted pre-score (auto-calculated before human review)
  aiPreScore: v.optional(v.number()),
  aiPreScoreBreakdown: v.optional(v.string()), // JSON string of AI analysis
  
  // Timing
  submittedAt: v.number(),
  reviewStartedAt: v.optional(v.number()),
  completedAt: v.optional(v.number()),
  
  // Batch tracking
  batchId: v.optional(v.string()),
  batchName: v.optional(v.string()),
  
  // Version tracking (for revision loops)
  version: v.number(), // starts at 1, increments on revision
  previousReviewId: v.optional(v.id("creativeReviews")),
})
  .index("by_status", ["status"])
  .index("by_creative", ["creativeId"])
  .index("by_batch", ["batchId"])
  .index("by_submitted", ["submittedAt"])
  .index("by_score", ["qualityScore"]),

// Review activity log
reviewActivity: defineTable({
  reviewId: v.id("creativeReviews"),
  action: v.union(
    v.literal("submitted"),
    v.literal("review_started"),
    v.literal("approved"),
    v.literal("rejected"),
    v.literal("revision_requested"),
    v.literal("revision_submitted"),
    v.literal("auto_approved"),
    v.literal("score_updated"),
    v.literal("note_added")
  ),
  details: v.optional(v.string()),
  timestamp: v.number(),
})
  .index("by_review", ["reviewId"])
  .index("by_timestamp", ["timestamp"]),

// Review settings / configuration
reviewSettings: defineTable({
  // Auto-approve threshold (creatives scoring above this skip human review)
  autoApproveThreshold: v.number(), // default: 90
  
  // Required minimum score to approve
  minimumApproveScore: v.number(), // default: 60
  
  // Scoring weights (must sum to 100)
  compositionWeight: v.number(),     // default: 25
  brandAlignmentWeight: v.number(),  // default: 25
  copyWeight: v.number(),            // default: 25
  platformFitWeight: v.number(),     // default: 25
  
  // Batch settings
  defaultBatchSize: v.number(), // default: 30 (Konstant's "30 ads" model)
  
  // Notification settings
  notifyOnNewBatch: v.boolean(),
  notifyOnAutoApprove: v.boolean(),
  
  // Active brand
  brandId: v.optional(v.string()),
})
```

## 1.4 New Backend Modules

### `convex/creativeReviews.ts`
```
Functions needed:
- submitForReview(creativeId, batchId?, batchName?) → creates review record
- submitBatchForReview(creativeIds[], batchName) → bulk submit
- startReview(reviewId) → marks as in_review
- approveCreative(reviewId, scores, notes?) → marks approved, updates creative status to "ready"
- rejectCreative(reviewId, reason, instructions?) → marks rejected
- requestRevision(reviewId, instructions) → marks revision_requested
- resubmitRevision(reviewId, updatedCreativeId) → creates new version
- autoScoreCreative(reviewId) → AI pre-scoring via internal action
- getReviewQueue(status?, batchId?) → paginated list
- getReviewStats() → dashboard metrics (pending, approved, rejected, avg score, avg review time)
- getBatchProgress(batchId) → batch-level metrics
- updateSettings(settings) → update review thresholds
- getSettings() → current settings
```

### `convex/creativeReviewActions.ts` (internal action for AI pre-scoring)
```
- aiPreScore(creativeId) → analyzes creative using AI:
  - Composition: checks visual balance, hierarchy, whitespace
  - Brand alignment: compares against stored brand guidelines
  - Copy quality: headline power, CTA clarity, character counts
  - Platform fit: aspect ratio, text overlay %, safe zones
  Returns: { score: number, breakdown: object, suggestions: string[] }
```

